post_text:
Main Prep Parents--
We are sad to announce that Gov. DeWine has closed school for the remainder of the year. Please know that your Main Prep school contact will continue to connect with you and your child daily until our last day on June 4. We will also offer meals on Mondays and Fridays for pick-up or delivery. School communications will come via text, e-mail, or Facebook posts.

We miss you all terribly and wish this outcome had been different. Please reach out if you need any support from us. You and your families are in our hearts always.

post_text:
Main Prep Families---
First and foremost, we hope you are staying safe and that all your family is healthy. With the most recent "stay-at-home" order by the governor, we will only be providing lunches on Friday for the next two weeks. Your school contact will be reaching out with details. We also have extra work packets if you need them.

In order to take accurate attendance, your child must check in with their school contact daily. This let's us know that your child is working through their daily school work and gives us an opportunity to answer any questions they may have! If we are unable to reach you, your child will be marked absent for the day.

We continue to keep all of you in our thoughts. Our hearts are heavy as we enter another week without seeing our children. Please reach out if you need anything at all. I can't wait to celebrate having our Main Prep family back together again!

Best---Rebecca Holthaus, principal

post_text:
Main Prep Parents--
This is just a reminder that Main Prep staff members will be reaching out to you or your child everyday. This allows us to check on your child's academic progress and to take attendance as these are still considered school days. Your child should ask any questions they have regarding their packet of work. This is also your opportunity to let us know if you need breakfast or lunch to pick up at the school or to be delivered. If your child has completed their provided packet, we are also happy to provide more school work.

From our hearts to your home---we miss every one of you every day. Please know that we are here for you if you need anything. We want to keep our Main Prep family together through this difficult absence! #weloveourpanthers #MainPrepfamily #wemissyou #bettertogether
